  "text": "It can be shown that R t (a) is derivable in the corresponding system BID if, and only if, the goal R(a) is left-terminating in the sense of Apt and Pedreschi [1] . Moreover, the formula R s (a) ∧ R t (a) is derivable in BID if, and only if, the goal R(a) succeeds and is left-terminating; R f (a) ∧ R t (a) is derivable in BID if, and only if, the goal R(a) fails finitely and is left-terminating. These results are proved in [CITATION_1] . What remains to show in this paper is that the system used in [CITATION_2] can be embedded into BID. In order to do this we need some terminology of logic programming. For a more detailed presentation we refer the reader to [CITATION_3] .",
